<br>
First off I'd like to say thanks for taking the time to check out our post.<br>
<br>
Alot of our fellow Firiona Vie players are probably thinking to themselves, &quot;Self, I've been seeing more and more folks running around with an &lt;Absolved&gt; tag next to their name; who are these people and what are they doing on my server? And what are they Absolved of, anyhow?&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, allow me to explain.<br>
<br>
Absolved is a guild formed on the idea that being &quot;successful&quot; in Everquest (I.E. Raiding) and maintaining a fun, tight-knit atmosphere are *not* mutually exclusive. Killing things is our goal; however, we will always be guided by a few important rules:<br>
1. Everquest is a game; albeit a very time consuming one. It is not a job and people will absolutely not be forced to treat it like one.<br>
<br>
2. Games are meant to be fun; we'll always weigh this factor when making any decisions that will effect our playing style. An underlying principle that must be understood, however, is that no game is fun all the time. A football player loves to play; however, he might not love to spend 4 hours a day in the gym in the offseason.. but in order to be successful, thats what he has to do. The same holds true in Everquest.<br>
<br>
3. The social interaction of Everquest is one of its most alluring factors; it's what makes the game so fun and so addictive. We'll strive to remember that there are human beings behind those toons.. and try to treat them like one.<br>
<br>
The overall, end goal of Absolved is to become a premier guild on the server; I could care less about the term uber - but we will be known as a guild who does things and does them well, who sets goals and accomplishes them and has fun in the process.<br>
<br>
A personal note to our members.. I'm going to strive to always make the guild a place you can relax and be yourself, that the game will always remain an escape from the pressures we all face in everyday life; and that together we'll go out and face all the challenges this game has to offer. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Update</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  At this point and time, we have developed a solid core of absolutely outstanding people and now we're looking to expand on that.  No formal level requirement; we're using the total person concept.  However, if you're not at least 55+ .. plan on getting there as soon as possible.  Absolved has everything to look forward to; so much content is now available and we all truly look forward to experiencing it with each other.  Please, hop on over to our forums at <br>
pub84.ezboard.com/babsolved<br>
Or shoot a tell to myself or any other Absolved member you see online if you have any questions or if you'd just like to get to know us.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
<br>
Daggz Nabbit<br>
Assassin of the Vale<br>
